{"id":25697,"date":"2017-12-29T21:13:14","date_gmt":"2017-12-29T17:13:14","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=25697"},"modified":"2021-10-27T11:32:32","modified_gmt":"2021-10-27T07:32:32","slug":"dua-for-adhan","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/29\/dua-for-adhan\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Prayer: Supplications during and after call to prayer"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abdullah ibn Amr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>When you hear the caller to prayer, repeat what he says and then send blessings upon me. Verily, whoever sends blessings upon me, Allah will send blessings upon him ten times. Then, ask Allah to grant me the means of approach<\/strong>, <strong>for it is a station in Paradise not befitting but for one servant among the servants of Allah. I hope I am that one servant. Whoever asks Allah to grant me the means of approach, the intercession is permitted for him<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 384<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Muslim<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0645\u0652\u0631\u0650\u0648 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e <strong>\u0625\u0650\u0630\u064e\u0627 \u0633\u064e\u0645\u0650\u0639\u0652\u062a\u064f\u0645\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064f\u0624\u064e\u0630\u0651\u0650\u0646\u064e \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f\u0648\u0627 \u0645\u0650\u062b\u065